titleStmt.title: His Highnesse the Prince of VVales His answer to the Earle of Warwicks summons: sent by Major Humphry Bosvvell, the 22. of September 1648. stilo novo: with the Earle of Warwicks desire to meet the Lord Willoughby. Another paper of the Earl of Warwicks, in answer to the Princes. A letter of Dorizlaus's intercepted, going to the Earle of Warwick, concerning the arresting of the Constant Warwick, and the captain, being prevented by the same letter. Also the Princes coming to his navy, with 10000.l. for the sea-men; and the Hollanders joyning with the Prince.
titleStmt.author: Charles II, King of England, 1630-1685.
